## Meet Backticks (`` ` ``)

Concatenating strings with `+` signs gets messy quickly. In 2015, JavaScript introduced **Template Literals** using backticks (the key above Tab on most keyboards).

Template Literals allow you to **inject variables directly into a string** using `${}`:

```javascript
let name = "Alice";
let score = 95;

// Old way (messy):
let oldWay = "Player " + name + " scored " + score + " points.";

// New way (elegant!):
let newWay = `Player ${name} scored ${score} points.`;
```

This is called **String Interpolation**, and it's the preferred way to combine text and variables! 🎯

